	<Slide>
		<Caption>.NET</Caption>
		<Type>Slide</Type>
		<Content>
			<![CDATA[
    <ul>
      <li><b>.NET / <i>.NET Framework</i></b></li>
      <ul>
        <li>Windows - year 2002</li>
        <li>Response to Java</li>
        <li>It was never truly <i>multi-platform</i></li>
      </ul>
      <li><b>.NET Core</b></li>
      <ul>
        <li>MONO project - <i>multi-platform</i></li>
        <li>Year 2017 - .NET Core ==> <i>multi-platform</i></li>
      </ul>
      <li><b>.NET</b></li>
      <ul>
        <li>Until version 3.1, it was still .NET Core</li>
        <li>From then on, only .NET</li>
        <ul>
          <li>.NET 5.0 - "old"</li>
          <li>.NET 6.0 - <b>LTS == LONG term support</b></li>
          <li>.NET 7.0 - <b>STS == STANDARD (~~ short) term support</b></li>
          <li>.NET 8.0 - "in development"</li>
        </ul>
      </ul>
    </ul>
    ]]>
		</Content>
	</Slide>


